        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 7 at 8:21PM CDT until August 7 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 820 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Powers Lake to 9 miles northwest of Ross to 9
miles southeast of Epping, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Stanley, Tioga, Ray, Powers Lake, Wildrose, Epping, Palermo,
Lostwood, White Earth Bay Recreation Area, White Tail Bay Recreation
Area, and Mcgregor.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
